<doc id="45274" wikidata="Q55623146" url="?curid=45274" title="Military fiat">
<text>Military fiat is a process whereby a decision is made and enforced by military means without the participation of other political elements. The Latin term &quot;fiat&quot;, translated as &quot;let it be,&quot; suggests the autocratic attitude ascribed to such a process. For example, many coups involve the imposition of a new government by military fiat.

